\f0 \cf0 \
Pour gel and let it polymerize for 1 hour. After set, be careful pulling out combs so that wells remain very flat. Assemble gel onto the gel rig. An aluminum plate backing can be used on the rig to insure proper heat distribution during run and more uniform mobility between the lanes. Use 0.5x TBE for running buffer. Rinse wells with running buffer to displace any urea that may have accumulated.  Pre-run the gel at 5W for at least 20 min.\
\
Prepare samples of 10-30\uc0\u956 g of total RNA (volume of 15 \u956 l or less) mixed with an equal volume of 2x Loading Dye (8 M urea, 25 mM EDTA, 0.025% xylene cyanol (XC), 0.025% bromophenol blue (BB)). Heat samples in 80
\fs16 \up11 \super o
\fs24 \up0 \nosupersub C heat block for 5-10 min, spin down, and use a beveled tip to load onto warm gel after urea from wells has been washed out again. Run gel at 2 W for 20 minutes (allows RNAs large and small to gently enter gel), and then raise to 12 W for ~1.5 hr, until the BB dye just runs off the gel. (XC dye should still be in the middle of the gel.)\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl278\sa275
\cf0 Separate gel onto Saran wrap and remove wells. Stain with 4 \uc0\u956 g/ml ethidium bromide in 0.5X TBE for 5 min and look for tRNA and 5S rRNA bands (78 and 120 nt) for quality of RNA prep and for visual loading control. Save image.\
\'95 
\b Transfer Gel to Membrane (revised, Dec. 2009)
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0
\cf0 Cut Amersham Hybond-NX membrane (GE Healthcare) and 4 sheets of 3mm Whatman Chromatography filter paper to size. The gel will swell slightly during the Ethidum staining, so be generous with sizing the membrane and filter paper. Label membrane with a pencil. \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl278\sa275
\cf0 Remove gel from staining solution but leave it on saran wrap. Presoak membrane and filter paper in 0.5X TBE. Place soaked membrane on the gel so that it overlaps the lanes containing loading dye. Note orientation of membrane on gel. Cut away any excess gel that extends beyond the edges of the membrane. Place 2 sheets of soaked filter paper on top of membrane. Flip gel/membrane/filter sandwich over and place onto bottom platform of Semidry apparatus (e.g., Bio-Rad Trans-Blot SD Semi-Dry Transfer Unit). Layer remaining 2 filter papers on top of gel. Use a cut plastic serological pipette and roll along the gel sandwich to smooth out bubbles. Add a bit more 0.5X TBE buffer to make sure sandwich is quite moist. \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl278
\cf0 Load top lid of Semidry apparatus, and hook up to a power supply that handles high current (e.g., Hoefer EPS 2A200, Amersham Pharmacia). Transfer at constant current (4 mA/cm\super 2\nosupersub  of membrane) for 45 minutes. The voltage should remain around 20V, but may get higher towards end of run. Do not let run longer, as the unit heats up and buffer will start to evaporate. Positive electrode is on the base unit (pulls nucleic acids down). \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri29

\f1 \cf0 During transfer, prepare EDC solution for cross-linking the RNA to membrane. First, make 1x methylimidazole stock: add 30 ml of dH\sub 2\nosupersub O to 408 \'b5l of 12.5 M 1-methylimidazole. pH to 8 with 1 M HCl. Bring total volume up to 40 ml with dH\sub 2\nosupersub O and filter sterilize. Stock solution can be kept at RT. For each membrane, make fresh EDC solution by adding 0.373 g of EDC (1-ethyl-3-(3-dimethylaminoprophy) carbodiimide) to 12 mL of  the 1x methylimidazole stock. This is enough for 1 membrane of about 16 cm\super 2\nosupersub . \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl278

\f0 \cf0 After transfer is complete, disassemble the gel sandwich and soak the gel in the ethidium stain for ~ 5 min. to make sure that the RNA has transferred from the gel. It is common to see a smear of material remaining near the well, but all of the discrete rRNA and tRNA bands should no longer be visible. Save image.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri29

\f1 \cf0 Place in order on top of one another: a piece of saran-wrap large enough to completely wrap the membrane, the membrane face down, Whatman paper cut to size of membrane. Pour the freshly prepared EDC solution onto the Whatman paper and completely saturate it. Wrap up the membrane sandwich with the wrap and incubate at 60C for 15 min to 2 hours. Disassemble sandwich and rinse membrane briefly several times with dH\sub 2\nosupersub O. Bake membrane at 80C for 10 min. if saving membrane for later. Otherwise membrane can go directly into pre-hybridization buffer.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri29

